results.name: Number of lambda-parking functions of the unique partition lambda with encoding n = Product_{i:lambda} prime(i).
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
example: n = 18 = 2*3*3 = prime(1)*prime(2)*prime(2) encodes partition [1,2,2] having seven lambda-parking functions: [1,1,1], [1,1,2], [1,2,1], [2,1,1], [1,2,2], [2,1,2], [2,2,1], thus a(18) = 7.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, Dec 02 2015
